      "role": "user",
      "content": "i used to feel like there was something humming inside me. like a constant vibration of color and intention. but it's just gone. i sit in front of the canvas and there's nothing. no spark, no hunger, nothing. it feels like the part of me that actually mattered just evaporated, leaving behind this heavy, breathing shell that doesn't even belong to me anymore. just a hollow vessel for no one.",
